FOURTEEN People have been shot dead at a Soweto tavern in the early hours of Sunday morning, 10 July 2021. The shooting happened at the Nomzamo tavern in Orlando East. It is alleged that patrons at the tavern in question were enjoying their drinks when gunmen opened fire at them, killing at least 14. According to reports, some people were rushed to hospital following the shooting incident. The Soweto tragedy happens after the burial of the 21 teenagers who also lost their lives at eNyobeni tavern in East London.  This is a developing story, more information to follow...